    "They support operations such as separating elements of the answer (e.g., to separate exercise and diet), removing punctuations (so that 'nutrition.'",
    "and 'nutrition' can map to the same construct), and eliminating obvious redundancy (e.g., obesity is a keyphrase in the text but not a cause for obesity itself).",
    "High-level filters involve advanced Natural Language Understanding and send additional prompts to GPT, hence results vary.",
    "These filters identify constructs in the answer that are equivalent to existing nodes in the map, to avoid including redundant nodes in the map (Fig. 4a).",
    "One form of equivalence is semantic similarity (Fig. 4b), which is based on closed related meanings (e.g., 'impulsivity' and 'acting suddenly without planning of considering the consequences')."
  ],
